body:
I have a shared team location for a spack mirror.  I ran into a problem last night when I noticed our axom@develop mirrored tarball had not been updated since May.  This is especially bad considering there is no way to notice this until a new feature or bug fix is needed from a dependency you track via a git branch.

### Steps to reproduce the issue

```console
$ spack create mirror -d /mirror/directory serac@develop%gcc
// notice time stamp on /mirror/directory/axom/develop.tar.gz
// do some change to axom's git develop branch
$ spack create mirror -d /some/local/directory serac@develop%gcc
// notice the time stamp on /mirror/directory/axom/develop.tar.gz has not changed
```

### Workaround

```console
$ spack create mirror -d /mirror/directory serac@develop%gcc
// notice time stamp on /mirror/directory/axom/develop.tar.gz
// do some change to axom's git develop branch
$ rm -rf /mirror/directory/axom/develop.tar.gz /mirror/directory/_source-cache/git/LLNL/axom.git/develop.tar.gz
$ spack create mirror -d /some/local/directory serac@develop%gcc
// notice the time stamp on /mirror/directory/axom/develop.tar.gz has changed
```
